# Generated by stepconf 1.1 at Wed Oct 18 19:03:20 2023
# If you make changes to this file, they will be
# overwritten when you run stepconf again
#
# ============================================================
# LATHE CONVERSION NOTES (Phenix Wood Lathe - X and Z axes)
# Pi 4B + Byte2Bot Parallel Hat + 5-axis breakout board
#
# Changes from cncRouter.hal:
#   1. stepgen reduced from 3 to 2 instances (no Y axis)
#   2. Y axis stepper pin wiring commented out (no Y axis on lathe)
#   3. Y axis stepper params/joints commented out (no Y axis on lathe)
#   4. Y limit switch input commented out (no Y axis on lathe)
#   5. Z axis renumbered: joint.2/stepgen.2 -> joint.1/stepgen.1
#      (Z is now the 2nd joint since Y was removed)
#   6. A and B axis stepper wiring commented out (unused on lathe)
#   7. Spindle PWM removed - lathe has 3 mechanical speeds toggled
#      externally; LinuxCNC only sends on/off via spindle relay
#   8. No physical limit switches on this lathe - all hardware limit
#      connections removed. Soft limits enforced via INI MIN_LIMIT/MAX_LIMIT.
#      The all-limit input (pin-24) and all neg/pos-lim-sw-in joints removed.
#
# REQUIRED INI FILE CHANGES (in your .ini config file):
#   [KINS]
#     KINEMATICS = trivkins coordinates=XZ
#     JOINTS = 2
#   [TRAJ]
#     COORDINATES = X Z
#   [JOINT_0]  (X axis)
#     MIN_LIMIT = -x.xxx   (set to your cross slide travel in machine units)
#     MAX_LIMIT =  x.xxx
#   [JOINT_1]  (Z axis)
#     MIN_LIMIT = -x.xxx   (set to your bed travel in machine units)
#     MAX_LIMIT =  x.xxx
# ============================================================

loadrt [KINS]KINEMATICS
loadrt [EMCMOT]EMCMOT base_period_nsec=[EMCMOT]BASE_PERIOD servo_period_nsec=[EMCMOT]SERVO_PERIOD num_joints=[KINS]JOINTS
loadrt charge_pump


